      "line": 76,
      "message": "I don't mind splitting it into two lines if it is not clear enough. In this case, the Type name has been repeated twice in the same line so I think don't lose any information.\n\nfinal DmiPluginRegistrationErrorResponse dmiPluginRegistrationErrorResponse = \nnew DmiPluginRegistrationErrorResponse()\n\nfinal var dmiPluginRegistrationErrorResponse = new DmiPluginRegistrationErrorResponse()\n\nIf I have to choose between splitting a line at one place and increasing the line length limit for the entire code, I would choose the first one.\n\n@Team \nPlease share your views with keeping in mind that it is specific to this scenario.",
